<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  NIL VPN — iOS PacketTunnel app-extension entitlements
  (bundle id: com.nilvpn.client.PacketTunnel, child of the container app id).

  INTEGRATION SCAFFOLDING. iOS counterpart of PacketTunnel.entitlements (the macOS System-Extension
  flavor). The ONE value that differs from macOS is the network-extension flavor:

  * com.apple.developer.networking.networkextension
      iOS uses `packet-tunnel-provider` (an app extension). macOS uses
      `packet-tunnel-provider-systemextension` (a system extension). They MUST match the target type
      or the extension will not load. This entitlement is DISCRETIONARY on iOS — it requires an Apple
      Developer *organization* account and is granted by Apple on request
      (email networkextension@apple.com); allow weeks of latency. Without it, signing fails.

  * com.apple.security.application-groups
      Identical group `group.com.nilvpn.client` as the container app, so app + appex share a
      container. Must match the app's value exactly.

  Privacy note (NIL SOUL): the appex is the only place packets flow. It receives just the node
  endpoint + pinned measurement + per-connection grant via providerConfiguration and never logs any
  of it (PD-2, PD-3). It carries no account, email, or payment identity — none is ever passed to it.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.developer.networking.networkextension</key>
	<array>
		<string>packet-tunnel-provider</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>group.com.nilvpn.client</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
